      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KINGDOM HEART (7) closed well from the wide gate with a sound third over 1000m at Warren. Well placed in this line-up from the good gate. Can get off the mark. BAWNAGLEN (1) resumes from a spell of four-and-a-half months. Back in class and trip after finishing fifth over 1600m at Scone. Can sprint well fresh in this company. BRILLIANT BEAGLE (5) did little and finished a dismal eleventh from the wide gate over 1100m at Tocumwal. Tongue-tie goes on from the better gate and capable of better. JACK THE BOSS (2) in need of the run first-up for the new yard with a plugging sixth over 1100m at Mudgee. Strips fitter and should be thereabouts. NANDOWRIE (3) lightly raced gelding resuming after finishing thereabouts at his last two outings. Back with the one trial and stays in the mix.",
